Context: The College engaged in a master campus planning process starting in 2012 to provide a vision for future space planning initiatives. The plan outlines key goals to meet current and future space planning needs while improving the learning environment. As an urban college, it aims to leverage assets of City of Toronto to deliver a 21st century education. Strategic campus improvements will create spaces for a smart economy. The Master Campus Plan was put forth in 2014. Students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
